         <note class="- topic/note ">The maximum cable length is
100 meters.</note>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Cable sizes in this manual are based on table
52–C2 of IEC 60364–5–52 with the following assertions:</p>
         <ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">90 °C conductors</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Use of copper conductors</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">An ambient temperature of 30 °C</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">400 V/230 V and grouping of four cables</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
         <p class="- topic/p ">If the ambient temperature is greater than 30 °C, larger
conductors are to be selected with the correction factors of the IEC.</p>
